#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.70"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.70:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.70:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.70:0.3"
msgid "70. Uposathasutta "
msgstr "70. Sabbath "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.70:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "an3.70:1.2"
msgid " ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.70:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho visākhā migāramātā tadahuposathe yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho visākhaṃ migāramātaraṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Visākhā, Migāra’s mother, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to her, "

msgctxt "an3.70:1.4"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, visākhe, āgacchasi divā divassā”ti? "
msgstr "“So, Visākhā, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.70:1.5"
msgid "“Uposathāhaṃ, bhante, ajja upavasāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Today, sir, I’m observing the sabbath.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.206, sc2
msgctxt "an3.70:2.1"
msgid "“Tayo khome, visākhe, uposathā. "
msgstr "“There are, Visākhā, these three sabbaths. "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.3"
msgid "Gopālakuposatho, nigaṇṭhuposatho, ariyuposatho. "
msgstr "The sabbath of the cowherds, the sabbath of the Jains, and the sabbath of the noble ones. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.70:2.4"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, gopālakuposatho hoti? "
msgstr "And what is the sabbath of the cowherds? "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, visākhe, gopālako sāyanhasamaye sāmikānaṃ gāvo niyyātetvā iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "It’s just like a cowherd who, in the late afternoon, takes the cows back to their owners. They reflect: "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.6"
msgid "‘ajja kho gāvo amukasmiñca amukasmiñca padese cariṃsu, amukasmiñca amukasmiñca padese pānīyāni piviṃsu; "
msgstr "‘Today the cows grazed in this place and that, and they drank in this place and that. "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.7"
msgid "sve dāni gāvo amukasmiñca amukasmiñca padese carissanti, amukasmiñca amukasmiñca padese pānīyāni pivissantī’ti; "
msgstr "Tomorrow the cows will graze in this place and that, and drink in this place and that.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.8"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, idhekacco uposathiko iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "In the same way, someone keeping the sabbath reflects: "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.9"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khvajja idañcidañca khādanīyaṃ khādiṃ, idañcidañca bhojanīyaṃ bhuñjiṃ; "
msgstr "‘Today I ate this and that, and had a meal of this and that. "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.10"
msgid "sve dānāhaṃ idañcidañca khādanīyaṃ khādissāmi, idañcidañca bhojanīyaṃ bhuñjissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "Tomorrow I’ll eat this and that, and have a meal of this and that.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.11"
msgid "So tena abhijjhāsahagatena cetasā divasaṃ atināmeti. "
msgstr "And so they spend their day with a mind full of covetousness. "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, gopālakuposatho hoti. "
msgstr "That’s the sabbath of the cowherds. "

msgctxt "an3.70:2.13"
msgid "Evaṃ upavuttho kho, visākhe, gopālakuposatho na mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro. (1) "
msgstr "When the cowherd’s sabbath is observed like this it’s not very fruitful or beneficial or splendid or bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.70:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, nigaṇṭhuposatho hoti? "
msgstr "And what is the sabbath of the Jains? "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.2"
msgid "Atthi, visākhe, nigaṇṭhā nāma samaṇajātikā. "
msgstr "There’s a kind of ascetic belonging to a group called the Jains. "

# NOTE: Rendered as plural by BB. At SN55.12 the text is also singular, but at AN 10.176 there is a variant in plural. To me the plural reads better in English.
msgctxt "an3.70:3.3"
msgid "Te sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti: "
msgstr "They encourage their disciples: "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.4"
msgid "‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, ye puratthimāya disāya pāṇā paraṃ yojanasataṃ tesu daṇḍaṃ nikkhipāhi; "
msgstr "‘Please, good people, don’t hurt any living creatures more than a hundred leagues away to the east. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.5"
msgid "ye pacchimāya disāya pāṇā paraṃ yojanasataṃ tesu daṇḍaṃ nikkhipāhi; "
msgstr "Don’t hurt any living creatures more than a hundred leagues away to the west. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.6"
msgid "ye uttarāya disāya pāṇā paraṃ yojanasataṃ tesu daṇḍaṃ nikkhipāhi; "
msgstr "Don’t hurt any living creatures more than a hundred leagues away to the north. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.7"
msgid "ye dakkhiṇāya disāya pāṇā paraṃ yojanasataṃ tesu daṇḍaṃ nikkhipāhī’ti. "
msgstr "Don’t hurt any living creatures more than a hundred leagues away to the south.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.8"
msgid "Iti ekaccānaṃ pāṇānaṃ anuddayāya anukampāya samādapenti, ekaccānaṃ pāṇānaṃ nānuddayāya nānukampāya samādapenti. "
msgstr "So they encourage kindness and compassion for some creatures and not others. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.9"
msgid "Te tadahuposathe sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti: "
msgstr "On the sabbath, they encourage their disciples: "

#. VAR: sabbacelāni → sabbaverāni (mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:3.10"
msgid "‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, sabbacelāni nikkhipitvā evaṃ vadehi—"
msgstr "‘Please, good people, take off all your clothes and say: "

#. VAR: kiñcanatasmiṃ → kiñcanattasmiṃ (bj) | kiñcanaṃ tasmiṃ (si, s1-3, pts1) | kiñcanatasmi (?)
#. VAR: katthaci → kismiñci (s1-3) | kassaci (pts1)
#. VAR: kiñcanatatthī’ti → kiñcana nātthīti (bj) | kiñcanatthīti (s1-3) | kiñcanaṃ natthīti (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.70:3.11"
msgid "nāhaṃ kvacani kassaci kiñcanatasmiṃ, na ca mama kvacani katthaci kiñcanatatthī’ti. "
msgstr "“I don’t belong to anyone anywhere! And nothing belongs to me anywhere!”’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.12"
msgid "Jānanti kho panassa mātāpitaro: "
msgstr "But their mother and father still know, "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.13"
msgid "‘ayaṃ amhākaṃ putto’ti; "
msgstr "‘This is our child.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.14"
msgid "sopi jānāti: "
msgstr "And they know, "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.15"
msgid "‘ime mayhaṃ mātāpitaro’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is my mother and father.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.16"
msgid "Jānāti kho panassa puttadāro: "
msgstr "Partner and child still know, "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.17"
msgid "‘ayaṃ mayhaṃ bhattā’ti; "
msgstr "‘This is our supporter.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.18"
msgid "sopi jānāti: "
msgstr "And they know, "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.19"
msgid "‘ayaṃ mayhaṃ puttadāro’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is my partner and child.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.20"
msgid "Jānanti kho panassa dāsakammakaraporisā: "
msgstr "Bondservants, workers, and staff still know: "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.21"
msgid "‘ayaṃ amhākaṃ ayyo’ti; "
msgstr "‘This is our master.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.22"
msgid "sopi jānāti: "
msgstr "And they know, "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.23"
msgid "‘ime mayhaṃ dāsakammakaraporisā’ti. "
msgstr "‘These are my bondservants, workers, and staff.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.24"
msgid "Iti yasmiṃ samaye sacce samādapetabbā musāvāde tasmiṃ samaye samādapenti. "
msgstr "So, at a time when they should be encouraged to speak the truth, the Jains encourage them to lie. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.25"
msgid "Idaṃ tassa musāvādasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This, I say, is lying. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.26"
msgid "So tassā rattiyā accayena bhoge adinnaṃyeva paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "When the night has passed they use their possessions once more, though they’ve not been given back to them. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.27"
msgid "Idaṃ tassa adinnādānasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This, I say, is stealing. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.28"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, nigaṇṭhuposatho hoti. "
msgstr "That’s the sabbath of the Jains. "

msgctxt "an3.70:3.29"
msgid "Evaṃ upavuttho kho, visākhe, nigaṇṭhuposatho na mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro. (2) "
msgstr "When the Jain’s sabbath is observed like this it’s not very fruitful or beneficial or splendid or bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.207, sc4
msgctxt "an3.70:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, ariyuposatho hoti? "
msgstr "And what is the sabbath of the noble ones? "

#. VAR: pariyodapanā → pariyodāpanā (?)
msgctxt "an3.70:4.2"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhassa, visākhe, cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "A corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:4.3"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:4.4"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the Realized One: "

msgctxt "an3.70:4.5"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:4.6"
msgid "Tassa tathāgataṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati. "
msgstr "As they recollect the Realized One, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:4.7"
msgid "seyyathāpi, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa sīsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s just like cleaning a dirty head by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.70:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa sīsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a dirty head cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:5.2"
msgid "Kakkañca paṭicca mattikañca paṭicca udakañca paṭicca purisassa ca tajjaṃ vāyāmaṃ paṭicca, evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa sīsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "With cleansing paste, clay, and water, and by applying the appropriate effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:5.3"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.70:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:6.2"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the Realized One: "

msgctxt "an3.70:6.3"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:6.4"
msgid "Tassa tathāgataṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the Realized One, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:6.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, visākhe: "
msgstr "This is called: "

#. VAR: brahmañcassa → brahmañca (mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:6.6"
msgid "‘ariyasāvako brahmuposathaṃ upavasati, brahmunā saddhiṃ saṃvasati, brahmañcassa ārabbha cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti’. "
msgstr "‘A noble disciple who observes the sabbath of Brahmā, living together with Brahmā. And because they think of Brahmā their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:6.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. (3.1) "
msgstr "That’s how a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.208, sc7
msgctxt "an3.70:7.1"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhassa, visākhe, cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "A corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:7.2"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:7.3"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the teaching: "

msgctxt "an3.70:7.4"
msgid "‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:7.5"
msgid "Tassa dhammaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti, seyyathāpi, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa kāyassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the teaching, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. It’s just like cleaning a dirty body by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.70:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa kāyassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a dirty body cleaned by applying effort? "

# NOTE: Cuṇṇa is churna, which in Ayurveda is usually a paste of predominately herbal composition. Sotti is Skt śūkti, i.e. pearl or oyster shell. Powdered pearl seems a little exotic as a basic bathing ingredient, so perhaps it included various kinds of powdered shells. These are also used today in Ayurveda.
msgctxt "an3.70:8.2"
msgid "Sottiñca paṭicca, cuṇṇañca paṭicca, udakañca paṭicca, purisassa ca tajjaṃ vāyāmaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "With pastes of powdered shells and herbs, water, and by applying the appropriate effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:8.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa kāyassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a dirty body is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:8.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.70:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:9.2"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the teaching: "

msgctxt "an3.70:9.3"
msgid "‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:9.4"
msgid "Tassa dhammaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the teaching, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:9.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, visākhe, ‘ariyasāvako dhammuposathaṃ upavasati, dhammena saddhiṃ saṃvasati, dhammañcassa ārabbha cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti’. "
msgstr "This is called: ‘A noble disciple who observes the sabbath of Dhamma, living together with Dhamma. And because they think of the Dhamma their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:9.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. (3.2) "
msgstr "That’s how a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.70:10.1"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhassa, visākhe, cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "A corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:10.2"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:10.3"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha: "

msgctxt "an3.70:10.4"
msgid "‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:10.5"
msgid "Tassa saṅghaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti, seyyathāpi, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa vatthassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the Saṅgha, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. It’s just like cleaning a dirty cloth by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.209, sc11
msgctxt "an3.70:11.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa vatthassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a dirty cloth cleaned by applying effort? "

# NOTE: Reading ūsa, see var.
msgctxt "an3.70:11.2"
msgid "Usmañca paṭicca, khārañca paṭicca, gomayañca paṭicca, udakañca paṭicca, purisassa ca tajjaṃ vāyāmaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "With salt, lye, cow dung, and water, and by applying the appropriate effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:11.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa vatthassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a dirty cloth is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:11.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.70:12.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:12.2"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha: "

msgctxt "an3.70:12.3"
msgid "‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, and worthy of veneration with joined palms. It is the supreme field of merit for the world.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:12.4"
msgid "Tassa saṅghaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the Saṅgha, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:12.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, visākhe, ‘ariyasāvako saṅghuposathaṃ upavasati, saṅghena saddhiṃ saṃvasati, saṅghañcassa ārabbha cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti’. "
msgstr "This is called: ‘A noble disciple who observes the sabbath of the Saṅgha, living together with the Saṅgha. And because they think of the Saṅgha their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:12.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. (3.3) "
msgstr "That’s how a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an3.70:13.1"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhassa, visākhe, cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "A corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:13.2"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:13.3"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako attano sīlāni anussarati akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni samādhisaṃvattanikāni. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects their own ethical conduct, which is unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "an3.70:13.4"
msgid "Tassa sīlaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti, seyyathāpi, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa ādāsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "As they recollect their ethical conduct, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. It’s just like cleaning a dirty mirror by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an3.70:14.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa ādāsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a dirty mirror cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:14.2"
msgid "Telañca paṭicca, chārikañca paṭicca, vālaṇḍupakañca paṭicca, purisassa ca tajjaṃ vāyāmaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "With oil, ash, a rolled-up cloth, and by applying the appropriate effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:14.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa ādāsassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a dirty mirror is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:14.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.210, sc15
msgctxt "an3.70:15.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:15.2"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako attano sīlāni anussarati akhaṇḍāni … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikāni. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects their own ethical conduct, which is unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "an3.70:15.3"
msgid "Tassa sīlaṃ anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti. "
msgstr "As they recollect their ethical conduct, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:15.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, visākhe, ‘ariyasāvako sīluposathaṃ upavasati, sīlena saddhiṃ saṃvasati, sīlañcassa ārabbha cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti’. "
msgstr "This is called: ‘A noble disciple who observes the sabbath of ethical conduct, living together with ethics. And because they think of their ethical conduct their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:15.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. (3.4) "
msgstr "That’s how a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an3.70:16.1"
msgid "Upakkiliṭṭhassa, visākhe, cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "A corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.2"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.3"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako devatā anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the deities: "

#. VAR: cātumahārājikā → cātummahārājikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: tatuttari → tatuttariṃ (bj, pts1) | taduttari (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.70:16.4"
msgid "‘santi devā cātumahārājikā, santi devā tāvatiṃsā, santi devā yāmā, santi devā tusitā, santi devā nimmānaratino, santi devā paranimmitavasavattino, santi devā brahmakāyikā, santi devā tatuttari. "
msgstr "‘There are the Gods of the Four Great Kings, the Gods of the Thirty-Three, the Gods of Yama, the Joyful Gods, the Gods Who Love to Create, the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others, the Gods of Brahmā’s Host, and gods even higher than these. "

#. VAR: tatthupapannā → tattha upapannā (bj) | tatthūpapannā (s3) | tatthuppannā (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.70:16.5"
msgid "Yathārūpāya saddhāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpā saddhā saṃvijjati. "
msgstr "When those deities passed away from here, they were reborn there because of their faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom. I, too, have the same kind of faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.6"
msgid "Yathārūpena sīlena samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpaṃ sīlaṃ saṃvijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.7"
msgid "Yathārūpena sutena samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpaṃ sutaṃ saṃvijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.8"
msgid "Yathārūpena cāgena samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpo cāgo saṃvijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.9"
msgid "Yathārūpāya paññāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpā paññā saṃvijjatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.70:16.10"
msgid "Tassa attano ca tāsañca devatānaṃ saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti, seyyathāpi, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa jātarūpassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom of both themselves and those deities, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. It’s just like cleaning dirty gold by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an3.70:17.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa jātarūpassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is dirty gold cleaned by applying effort? "

#. VAR: gerukañca paṭicca, nāḷikasaṇḍāsañca → nāḷikañca paṭicca saṇḍāsañca (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:17.2"
msgid "Ukkañca paṭicca, loṇañca paṭicca, gerukañca paṭicca, nāḷikasaṇḍāsañca paṭicca, purisassa ca tajjaṃ vāyāmaṃ paṭicca. "
msgstr "With a furnace, flux, a blowpipe, and tongs, and by applying the appropriate effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:17.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa jātarūpassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how dirty gold is cleaned by applying effort. "

msgctxt "an3.70:17.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.211, sc18
msgctxt "an3.70:18.1"
msgid "Kathañca, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a corrupt mind cleaned by applying effort? "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.2"
msgid "Idha, visākhe, ariyasāvako devatā anussarati: "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple recollects the deities: "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.3"
msgid "‘santi devā cātumahārājikā, santi devā tāvatiṃsā … pe … santi devā tatuttari. "
msgstr "‘There are the Gods of the Four Great Kings, the Gods of the Thirty-Three, the Gods of Yama, the Joyful Gods, the Gods Who Love to Create, the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others, the Gods of Brahmā’s Host, and gods even higher than these. "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.4"
msgid "Yathārūpāya saddhāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpā saddhā saṃvijjati. Yathārūpena sīlena … sutena … cāgena … paññāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tatthupapannā, mayhampi tathārūpā paññā saṃvijjatī’ti. "
msgstr "When those deities passed away from here, they were reborn there because of their faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom. I, too, have the same kind of faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.5"
msgid "Tassa attano ca tāsañca devatānaṃ saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarato cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti. "
msgstr "As they recollect the faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom of both themselves and those deities, their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, visākhe, ‘ariyasāvako devatuposathaṃ upavasati, devatāhi saddhiṃ saṃvasati, devatā ārabbha cittaṃ pasīdati, pāmojjaṃ uppajjati, ye cittassa upakkilesā te pahīyanti’. "
msgstr "This is called: ‘A noble disciple who observes the sabbath of the deities, living together with the deities. And because they think of the deities their mind becomes clear, joy arises, and mental corruptions are given up.’ "

msgctxt "an3.70:18.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, upakkiliṭṭhassa cittassa upakkamena pariyodapanā hoti. (3.5) "
msgstr "That’s how a corrupt mind is cleaned by applying effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an3.70:19.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, visākhe, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then that noble disciple reflects: "

msgctxt "an3.70:19.2"
msgid "‘yāvajīvaṃ arahanto pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā nihitadaṇḍā nihitasatthā lajjī dayāpannā sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharanti; "
msgstr "‘As long as they live, the perfected ones give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They are scrupulous and kind, and live full of compassion for all living beings. "

msgctxt "an3.70:19.3"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharāmi. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. I’ll be scrupulous and kind, and live full of compassion for all living beings. "

msgctxt "an3.70:19.4"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an3.70:20.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭiviratā dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharanti; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving. "

msgctxt "an3.70:20.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharāmi. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up stealing. I’ll take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. I’ll keep myself clean by not thieving. "

msgctxt "an3.70:20.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
#. VAR: ārācārī → anācārī (mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:21.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī ārācārī viratā methunā gāmadhammā; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex. "

msgctxt "an3.70:21.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up unchastity. I will be celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex. "

msgctxt "an3.70:21.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.212, sc22
msgctxt "an3.70:22.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭiviratā saccavādī saccasandhā thetā paccayikā avisaṃvādakā lokassa; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words. "

msgctxt "an3.70:22.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up lying. I’ll speak the truth and stick to the truth. I’ll be honest and trustworthy, and won’t trick the world with my words. "

msgctxt "an3.70:22.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an3.70:23.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ pahāya surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones give up alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an3.70:23.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ pahāya surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an3.70:23.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "an3.70:24.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and from food at the wrong time. "

msgctxt "an3.70:24.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ ekabhattiko rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time. "

msgctxt "an3.70:24.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an3.70:25.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto naccagītavāditavisūkadassanamālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows; and beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, fragrance, and makeup. "

msgctxt "an3.70:25.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ naccagītavāditavisūkadassanamālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows; and beautifying and adorning myself with garlands, fragrance, and makeup. "

msgctxt "an3.70:25.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissati. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an3.70:26.1"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ arahanto uccāsayanamahāsayanaṃ pahāya uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭiviratā nīcaseyyaṃ kappenti mañcake vā tiṇasanthārake vā; "
msgstr "As long as they live, the perfected ones give up high and luxurious beds. They sleep in a low place, either a cot or a straw mat. "

msgctxt "an3.70:26.2"
msgid "ahampajja imañca rattiṃ imañca divasaṃ uccāsayanamahāsayanaṃ pahāya uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato nīcaseyyaṃ kappemi mañcake vā tiṇasanthārake vā. "
msgstr "I, too, for this day and night will give up high and luxurious beds. I’ll sleep in a low place, either a cot or a straw mat. "

msgctxt "an3.70:26.3"
msgid "Imināpi aṅgena arahataṃ anukaromi, uposatho ca me upavuttho bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "I will observe the sabbath by doing as the perfected ones do in this respect.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
msgctxt "an3.70:27.1"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, visākhe, ariyuposatho hoti. "
msgstr "That’s the sabbath of the noble ones. "

msgctxt "an3.70:27.2"
msgid "Evaṃ upavuttho kho, visākhe, ariyuposatho mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso mahājutiko mahāvipphāro. "
msgstr "When the sabbath of the noble ones is observed like this it’s very fruitful and beneficial and splendid and bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.213, sc28
msgctxt "an3.70:28.1"
msgid "Kīvamahapphalo hoti kīvamahānisaṃso kīvamahājutiko kīvamahāvipphāro? "
msgstr "How much so? "

#. VAR: pahūtarattaratanānaṃ → pahūtasattaratanānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | pahūtamahāsattaratanānaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: issariyādhipaccaṃ → issarādhipaccaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.70:28.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, visākhe, yo imesaṃ soḷasannaṃ mahājanapadānaṃ pahūtarattaratanānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreyya, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Suppose you were to rule as sovereign lord over these sixteen great countries—Aṅga, Magadha, Kāsī, Kosala, Vajjī, Malla, Ceti, Vaṅga, Kuru, Pañcāla, Maccha, Sūrusena, Assaka, Avanti, Gandhāra, and Kamboja—full of the seven treasures. "

#. VAR: macchānaṃ → maccānaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: etaṃ → etassa (bj) | ekaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:28.3"
msgid "aṅgānaṃ, magadhānaṃ, kāsīnaṃ, kosalānaṃ, vajjīnaṃ, mallānaṃ, cetīnaṃ, vaṅgānaṃ, kurūnaṃ, pañcālānaṃ, macchānaṃ, sūrasenānaṃ, assakānaṃ, avantīnaṃ, gandhārānaṃ, kambojānaṃ, aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgatassa uposathassa etaṃ kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasiṃ. "
msgstr "This wouldn’t be worth a sixteenth part of the sabbath with its eight factors. "

msgctxt "an3.70:28.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.70:28.5"
msgid "Kapaṇaṃ, visākhe, mānusakaṃ rajjaṃ dibbaṃ sukhaṃ upanidhāya. "
msgstr "Because human kingship is a poor thing compared to the happiness of the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
#. VAR: rattindivo → rattidivo (mr)
msgctxt "an3.70:29.1"
msgid "Yāni, visākhe, mānusakāni paññāsa vassāni, cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ eso eko rattindivo. "
msgstr "Fifty years in the human realm is one day and night for the gods of the Four Great Kings. "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.2"
msgid "Tāya rattiyā tiṃsarattiyo māso. "
msgstr "Thirty such days make up a month. "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.3"
msgid "Tena māsena dvādasamāsiyo saṃvaccharo. "
msgstr "Twelve such months make up a year. "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.4"
msgid "Tena saṃvaccharena dibbāni pañca vassasatāni cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "The life span of the gods of the Four Great Kings is five hundred of these divine years. "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.5"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, visākhe, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco itthī vā puriso vā aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "It’s possible that a woman or man who has observed the eight-factored sabbath will—when their body breaks up, after death—be reborn in the company of the gods of the Four Great Kings. "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.6"
msgid "Idaṃ kho panetaṃ, visākhe, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ: "
msgstr "This is what I was referring to when I said: "

msgctxt "an3.70:29.7"
msgid "‘kapaṇaṃ mānusakaṃ rajjaṃ dibbaṃ sukhaṃ upanidhāya’. "
msgstr "‘Human kingship is a poor thing compared to the happiness of the gods.’ "

